values:
Whew. Sorry I haven't updated or commented lately. I've had shingles. I finally move out to enjoy myself and I'm miserable and broken out and in pain. I haven't wanted to do anything, my skin has been on fire and bleeding. RAAAH! The apartment is a mess. The dishes are stacked a mile high.

I'm going to go pass out. -_-
Find your Celestial Choir Happy Easter everyone!

Guess what? I'm writing from my OWN place!!

The apartment is ok. It's on the small side but I get to call it my own. The first night here everyone came over and basically hot boxed the place. Then they wouldn't go home. I had a lot of fun but I was so tired from moving that I wanted to sleep. I should be done unpacking everything by the end of the week. Then I'll start decorating. It's creepy having all white walls. My Dad is really dissapointed that I left. But I don't care. It's me time now.
I hope that me and Steve will be alright living together. I'm so excited that I get to see him every night. 

More later I have more to do!

Sorry I haven't written. I've been so busy! We actually found a place! I'm actually moving out of here! I'm so excited! I have so much to do in...A WEEK!!!! 
(^_^);;
How do I pack everything in a week? 

More details later..I am BUSY!
Woo hoo!!

Here I am again. I don't have many interesting things to report. Steve and I went apartment/trailor hunting. We found a few apartments we really like...and they're around here! I'm so excited. I'd love to get the hell out of Delaware not move even farther down into deserted land.
   I need a better layout. Anyone know where I can get a neat one? I'm not too great on making my own stuff (unless I wanted to embarrass myself) so I guess I'll poke around until I find something worthwhile.

Well I better run my Mother is nagging at me. 

I CANNOT WAIT TO GET OUT OF HERE.
What type of Fae are you?

It's Friday. I'm just waiting for Steve to get off of work so we can go and get some FOOD. We're going to look at apartments/trailers tomorrow. He wants to move down to Harrington to live closer to his brother. I hate living in hickville as it is and there is nothing to do down there. Well this entry sucks but I don't have a lot of time.

Since this is my first entry I figured I'd do a survey to explain myself in the quickest way possible.



A - AVAILABLE: Nope <3

B - BEST FRIEND(s): Shelby, Steve, Dan (sadly I have more guy friends)

C - CRUSH: no need

D - DOG'S NAME: Jet

E - EASIEST PERSON TO TALK TO: Steve

F- FAVORITE BAND: I like all kinds of music... hair metal/punk/rock: Metallica, Pantera, Johnny Cash, Goo Goo Dolls, Blondie, The Cars, Alanis, Emery, Green Day, Oasis, Smashing Pumpkins, The Who, Pink Floyd

G - GUMMY BEARS OR GUMMY WORMS: Gummy Bears all the way. Especially the red ones.

H - HOMETOWN: Dover, DE

I - INSTRUMENT: Guitar and the clarinet. Aren't I cool.

J - JUGGLE: I wish

K - KISSED SOMEONE: Yes

L - LONGEST CAR RIDE: Florida. My ass hurt for hours.

M - MILK FLAVOR: Strawberry

N - NUMBER OF SIBLINGS: One brother--Benjamin

O - ONE WISH: I could find people serious enough to keep a band going. That or my art was published.

P - PERSON WHO CALLED ME LAST: Steve

Q - FAVORITE QUOTE: "The great irony of life is barely no one makes it out alive"

S - SONG YOU LAST HEARD: Rapture-Blondie

T - TIME YOU WOKE UP: 12

U - UNKNOWN FACT ABOUT ME: I actually have feelings. 

V - VEGETABLE YOU HATE: brussel sprouts *gag* even the name is disgusting

W - WORST HABIT: Biting my nails and not being able to sit still

X - X-RAYS YOU'VE HAD: my arm and my leg

Y - YUMMY FOOD: chinese food. Sweet and sour chicken is my drug.

Z - ZODIAC SIGN: Virgo the virgin... *laughs*
